decision_conditions: Prior to the occupation of Phase 2, a scheme shall be submitted to and approved by the LPA demonstrating that all car parking spaces lost in Phase 1 will be re provided in future phases. Reason: To ensure the provision of adequate off-street/on-site parking in the interests of the safety and operation of the highway network, in accordance with policies T4 and T6 of the London Plan 2021 and policies CS7 and DM9 of the LDF Core Strategy 2012.

description: Non-Material Amendment to Planning Permission 20/02942/FUL (Part detailed/part outline planning permission for mixed use development, incl demolition of existing buildings and erection of up to 2170 residential units (Use Class C3), 290sqm of flexible office floorspace (Use Class E), 1395sqm of flexible retail/commercial floorspace (Use Class E/Sui Generis), 1250sqm community floorspace (Use Class F2), new publicly accessible open space and associated access, servicing, landscaping and works, incl stopping up of all public highway incl Somerset Rd, Wimpole Close, Eureka Rd. St. Peters Rd, Burritt Rd, Stapleford Close, Willingham Way, Chesterton Terrace, Excelsior Close, Washington Rd, Somerset Rd and Franklin Close, various footpaths, parking courts and other areas of highway) (the full description of development for planning permission 20/02942/FUL has been abridged. Please refer to planning permission 20/02942/FUL for the full description of development). Proposed changes to allow addition of second staircase, internal alteration to stair cores, removal of basement, relocation of car parking and services, reconfiguration of ground floor layout, minor increase to building footprints of Block C1,C2 and C3, re-alignment of Washington Rd to include a suitable turning space and loading space. Re-provision of accessible car parking space, removal of Tree T61.
